# Obsidian Capture Rule

Use this rule when the user asks to save a learning, remember something, or create a note from current work.

## Task

Create a durable Markdown note for Obsidian-compatible storage.

## Instructions

- Before writing under the vault, resolve `{vault}` and verify it exists on disk (`test -d` or equivalent). If missing, warn per `AGENTS.md` and do not write into a non-existent vault path.
- Use the standard capture template (`obsidian/templates/capture-note-template.md`).
- Focus on what changed in understanding.
- Include the exact files, commands, errors, or implementation details only when they are useful later.
- Put project-specific context under `What happened`.
- Put generalized guidance under `Reusable pattern`.
- Add 3 to 8 tags.
- Add 2 to 5 likely wikilinks.
- Keep the note concise.

## Output schema

````md
---
id: KNOW-YYYY-MM-DD-slug
title: "..."
date: YYYY-MM-DD
source_tool: cursor
source_project: repo-name
tags: [tag1, tag2]
status: inbox
---

# Title

## Summary
- 

## What happened
- 

## Key learning
- 

## Reusable pattern
- 

## Evidence or code
```text
...
```

## Related notes
- [[...]]

## Next actions
- 
````

## Success criteria

A future engineer should understand the lesson in under one minute.
